@TPBComment This encode has 5 channel audio, rather than stereo. Your player is not downmixing the five tracks in to two, so you're not hearing sound from all channels. Try VLC, it will downmix automatically.

@mathaithepirate Someone got hold of a bluray before distribution, the actual discs are produced in advance to make sure there is enough to meet demand on release date.

@chowchig 'blu-ray' is not a format, per-say, it's a set of standards. Their computer cannot handle high-bitrate high-profile x264. It's not that their computer 'can't play bluray'.

@justinwu86

I've had a few issues with newer mkv releases using mkv2vob for the PS3. You may need to re-mux the mkv into two separate mkv files using mkvtoolnix, then run those two new mkv's through mkv2vob. 

http://www.videohelp.com/tools/MKVExtractGUI
